    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Members of a species of tree squirrel that is the largest in size among species native to western North America. They are relatively shy, and will generally run up a tree and give a hoarse barking call when disturbed.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
